Australia Yield Spreads - Give up ground to U . S . . - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - AUD VS 3 - YR 10 - YR * AUD 3 - YR / 10 - YR SPREAD USD - 50 ( + 02 ) 40 ( + 06 ) * FUTURES 94 ( + 04 ) CAD 68 ( - 01 ) 66 ( - 01 ) * CASH 117 ( + 05 ) NZD - 178 ( - 10 ) - 49 ( - 06 ) * - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Australian bonds underperformed against U . S . debt as the market awaited developments there in the wake of Friday ' s massive sell - off in U . S . stocks , although they held their own versus other dollar bloc members . The local market had outpaced the U . S . late last week after data showed wages growth under control but remained well above the low of around 25 basis points seen a few weeks ago . Analysts at Hambros Bank believe moderate economic growth , excellent inflation propects and the possibility of a sixth easing suggest the Aussie market should continue to outperform . " However , in an environment of rising U . S . yields in coming months as the growth pulse picks up and inflationary corncerns emerge , the Australian market may underperform , " they said in a report . U . S . Treasury yields eased slightly in Tokyo trading on Monday after the mixed finish in New York on Friday . Spreads to Canada narrowed , which had also dragged it heels to the U . S . on Friday , while the negative spreads to New Zealand grew . N . Z . yields ended higher , although comments by the RBNZ that monetary policy conditions were too loose drew a muted response . - - Colin Brinsden 61 - 2 9373 - 1800 
